Defendant Jennifer J. Rauch in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant Jennifer J. Rauch in custody.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing.
Court sentenced defendant to serve 9 (NINE) DAYS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for 9 (NINE) days served.  TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges by 10-13-2016 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.

Defendant Jennifer J. Rauch in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant Jennifer J. Rauch in custody.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Court holds colloquy with Defendant.  Defendant does not want to wait for Residential treatment.  State moves to revoke the agreement.  The defendant is not in compliance with the terms of the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  Based upon the defendant's non-compliance, the court revoked the Deferred Prosecution Agreement; proceedings reinstated.  Court orders entry of judgment of conviction.

Defendant Jennifer J. Rauch in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin. sdg
State reports that Defendant was to submit documentation of actions during the DPA.  Defense reports that Defendant would like to be given a chance to enter a residential treatment detoxification center.  Bail remains the same EXCEPT COURT ORDERS turnover to JusticePoint.  Review hearing scheduled for October 13, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jennifer J. Rauch in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defendant has been mostly compliant with Deferred Prosecution Agreement, matter is adjourned for final review hearing in Branch 33.  Review hearing scheduled for October 5, 2015 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant Jennifer J. Rauch in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defendant will be admitted into detox within the next 48 hours.  Court ordered case adjourned for review hearing to Branch 33.  Review hearing scheduled for September 1, 2015 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Jennifer J. Rauch in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defense counsel requests a brief adjournment. State has no objection. Court grants request.  Review hearing scheduled for August 18, 2015 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant Jennifer J. Rauch in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC.

  Parties are prepared to enter into a deferred prosecution agreement.
Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum  and Elements/Jury Instructions, received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information.  Court WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement received, signed and filed.  All parties notified, effective August 1, 2015 this case is assigned to Judge Carl Ashley, Branch 33, in room 113 in the Safety Building.  Any right of substitution begins to run as of the date of receipt of this notice, unless notified by the court on an earlier date.  Court ordered case adjourned for review hearing in Branch 33.  Review hearing scheduled for August 3, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jennifer J. Rauch in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: TC. Defense counsel has received discovery and offer.  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea/dpa in Branch 37.  Plea hearing scheduled for June 5, 2015 at 08:30 am.

The Court ordered defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
Remaining bail to be returned to the remitter.

Defendant Jennifer J. Rauch in court.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.   Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance.  Defendant IS Public Defender eligible.  Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  The case is adjourned to Br. 37 for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for April 29, 2015 at 08:30 am.
